Protesters blocked the traffic flow along the N6 and a truck was set on fire between East London and  Newlands on Tuesday near Wings Park Airfield and Alton Quarry. The Eastern Cape transport department advised motorists to be cautious when approaching the area and consider using alternative routes. The department posted  pictures of a burning truck and firefighters putting out the fire on social media. It was not clear whether the truck was torched by the protesters at the time of publishing. Provincial transport department spokesperson Unathi Binqose said more information would be furnished as soon as possible. This is a developing story. DispatchLIVE